//Spring MVC Form Validation
  1.spring version 4 and higher supports bean validation API
  2.bean validation features: 1)required
                              2)validate length
                              3)validate numbers
                              4)validate with regular expressions
                              5)custom validation
  3.validation annotations: 1)@NotNull: checks that the annotated value is not null
                            2)@Min: must be a number >= value
                            3)@Max: must be a number <= value
                            4)@Size: size must mach the given size
                            5)@Pattern: must match a regular expression pattern
                            6)@Future/@Past: date must be in future or past of given date
                            7)others
  4.our road map: 1)set up our development environment
                  2)required field
                  3)validate number range: min, max
                  4)validate using regular expression(regexp)
                  5)custom validation
  
